{
  "stem": "5810.1",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we were released from Malines.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "One brother, at that time, and two sisters were taken to concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I now have proof that-- well, we know they never came back.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The chronology was that we had to come back to Brussels from Malines.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we hoped and then thought that we had a place to come back to, our home, the one that we had left.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Still 1942.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I would believe that, since they were taken by convoy in October of 1942, it must have been the month of October.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Maybe somewhere in that particular area.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I remember coming back to the house that we had escaped from in Belgium, and thought that we could just walk into our home.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now, another lesson for me was that I knew there was anti-Semitism in Belgium long before the Germans invaded.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE] But I didn't know to what extreme and what extent.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And in that house, where we had the store and the factory, we also had tenants-- gentile Belgian tenants-- living upstairs.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And when we came back to the house, those gentiles, Belgian tenants, came down and said this was no longer our home, that they had taken over, that we were just dirty Jews, and they didn't care what happened to us, but we were not coming into the house any longer.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And of course, we were shocked, surprised.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And my brother, who was, I believe, about 10 years older, 8 years older than I was, and somewhat of a-- [LAUGHS] a short fuse hothead, who believed that this was completely outrageous, had an altercation with the people on the street, in the doorway, wanting to go into the house.",
      "word_count": 51
    }
  ],
